<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 06 at 8:24PM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF WESTERN PIERCE AND
SOUTHEASTERN MCHENRY COUNTIES THROUGH 900 PM CDT...
At 823 PM CDT, strong thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 8 miles southeast of Towner to near Drake. Movement
was northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Rugby and Balta.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
